content: I didn't expect to complete this programme as I've never really been a runner. However, with a little perseverance, the course gave me the tips and encouragement I needed to succeed.
Love this app, supports you through the whole experience and motivates you.
Amazing app if you're a novice at running like me! I also have back and joint issues but this app has helped me to start slowly and not rush
Very well planned yup lead you to success. Go for it!
Very smooth progression, goid voice support
Has certainly got me motivated.
Unbelievable. I am NOT a runner but started this during lockdown like many others. I am currently on week 4 and am amazed that I cam actually run! A very well thought out app. Brilliant
Good but difficult to link music to.

Absolutely loved this app. I've haven't ran for a long while and really wanted to ease myself back into it again, this app was fantastic in helping me gain the confidence to run again. These step by step challenges are brilliant and give you a sense of achievement.
Excellent and easy to use

Happy with it, I started running with the NHS c25k podcast and was pleased to see coach Laura was still an option 😊 Now years later, I'm restarting safely after an injury, I'm enjoying training "with" Jo Wiley and my own playlists. I've done 5 runs so far using the app + Spotify + Strava and nothing crashed
This is an excellent app - helped me from 0 to 5km in 9 weeks. What's not to like? :-) Improvements? The ability to keep the screen on would be great. But this really is nit-picking.
I've enjoyed my first week and feel good
The system really does work
Audio and availability of speakers very temperamental

I loved using this app. I wasn't sure that as an unfit and overweight 50 year old I'd ever be able to run 5k. The app is so well paced and makes the 5k totally achievable if you stick with it. The marvelous Jo Whiley was my running buddy and I thank her for sticking with me! Seriously, as a non runner, to acheive a 5k run is just an amazing personal acheivement. I feel so pleased with myself and you will too if you use the app. I don't hesitate to give it (and Jo!) 5 stars!
Love it . Just the push I needed to get fit .Builds up slowly but eases you into completing the task.

Couch yo 5k does exactly what I'd hoped: in gently reintroducing, and encouraging, me to running. I always hated running, although I had previously participated in group runs to keep fit. Now I have diabetes, keeping fit is a no longer a choice, so I'm thankful this app exists.

Really well designed programme, Jo Whiley was my choice of coach (there are lots of different people you can choose from!) and super encouraging. It's worth buddying up with someone if possible to encourage and keep each other accountable and off the couch. Even if you've never run before or are really unfit, this will get you running comfortably!
It is a very good app
Good app to help get you off your feet, however in my case struggles to work in background when phone is locked.
Excellent
Amazing app to get you start running
Great just the motivation I needed to get up and get running going to try Laura on my next run .
Excellent experience and good coaching
This app works well in encouraging you but after a while the repetition gets to you and you no longer feel motivated to complete it.
It is very good at guiding me as I run. The regime is tough at times but it seems to be working.

I have just finished my last run and have found it really motivating to get up and go 3 times a week ,what a good app ,its made the whole experience fun to do . I have a Spotify playlist running alongside of it and I like how it fades the music so you can hear the coach(Sarah Millican for me ) giving instructions and encouragement then music comes back to normal volume again. I have recommended the app to just about everyone I know and intend to keep using it .

The way it gradually increases each week is perfectly worked out for the best chance of success. Jo wiley was an excellent coach as you can tell she's been there and done it. I am amazed at how much fitter I feel after 9 weeks following the programme I highly recommend it to everyone
It's not a walk in the park but a well supported build up (thank you Michael Johnson) to get you there. Go for it!
Very good in building up confidence and stamina to complete the challenge. Would never have done it without Jo Whiley encouraging me!
Brilliant way to get running. All you need brought together in one place; information, support (thanks Jo Whiley) & stretching. Thanks
Clear and easy to follow
Hard going but definitely gave me a challenge in lockdown
Excellent app with an excellent training plan and lots of inspiration and guidance just when its needed.
It worked a charm to help me achieve my 5K goal, the motivational nudges are very well placed to keep you going on those cold mornings. And I will keep using it for sure.

Have run for years but knees knackered so had to stop and do miss it. So.....me and 'Michael' started the couch to 5k bout 2 weeks ago and I so love it. It's so encouraging and stops me from doing too much too soon. Thanks so much. Anne Judge
Really good for me to get in the mood for running

Absolutely brilliant app and plan! I had Sarah Millican in my ear as my trainer and it was so good. Week 4 was the most difficult jump for me, but I did it after the third try and repeated it before moving on. I never thought I'd be able to run for 30 mins and this did it for me!

Ive always wanted to do the couch to 5k. But always found any excuse not to. But with all this covid 19 stuff. I thought lifes to short. This is a great app, and having sarah Milligan as my trainer, is a bonus. She keeps me motivated. Give it a go.

If you are considering taking up running definitely download this app. I could barely run for 2 minutes at the start without being shattered but by the end of the 9 weeks I was actually able to run easily run 5k and even did a 10k. I've always had knee issues when I've tried to take it up in the past but doing it like this, at a steady pace, has meant I've had no problems. Can't recommend it enough!
A fantastic app to help anyone to run 5k.
Would recommend for anyone who wants to take up running.
Couple of bugs but absolutely fantastic app!
Brilliant get you started app
Good pace and easy to use. Issues with it cutting out mid run on android phone
This app is really good, I like the fact that the announcements play over my own music so I can pick what I like to listen to. I would give it 5* but some of my runs haven't saved.
Helps to get you running but cuts out sometimes.
It's a brilliant app, only criticism is maybe the trainer could let you know where you're at a little bit more often on the longer runs and could put a bit more of the trainer's personality into it.
Really motivational and easy to use
Fab
Really motivating me to try running/jogging a bit.
Last few weeks are tough but you get a great sense of achievement

Unable to run before (and breathe at the same time).. this app is excellent for starting off not only learning to.run. it to breathe and modulate your pace . Stick at it even if sometimes staying indoors seems preferable; however make sure your kit is correct first. Good luck ! P.s Sarah Millican is such a gem, perfect accompanying encouragement :-)
Very helpful
Keeps you going
Couldn't have done it without it!
Great fun...and really enjoy having Sarah milligan as my coach 😂
So motivational feel great using this app
Jo Whiley such a great mentor to keep you going on each single run. I repeated lots of weeks which worked for me, so you can be as flexible as you like.
Love it 😀
Great programme. I thought no way can I do this in week 1, and yesterday in week 9 I just ran 5km. Trust the programme 👍🏻
Really enjoy it
Its been fab thanks pet
AMAZING. I couldn't run for 2 minutes, I'm now doing 40 minutes. Went from 20stone to 16 stone. Happy running 🏃‍♂️

Amazing at first I really didn't think I would achieve it in the first week I couldn't run for a minute now I can run for 30 minutes without stopping at all and with ease not out of breath when I've finished (well I am but I'm not dying on the floor like I assumed I would be.) It is also good as you can go back as in the third week I didn't think I was ready to do the increased run so I did week 2 again and it helped me to strengthen my core and continue till the end.
Was not convinced this would work I never ran in my life and I'm 44 years old! Today I ran for 20 minutes without stopping and without this app I would never have thought that possible!
Like it but it doesnt tell you how many calories you have burnt and doeant show you the map of your run

Having started again after an injury in week 3, I have now done the first 2 weeks 3 times and have found the app kept stopping in the week 1 runs. It happen multiple times in each run and would need to be restarted and skipped through each time (which meant I had to keep track of which walk or run I was up to) which I found very annoying. It seemed to sort itself for week 2 though and the first week 3 run which is as far as I've got so far. Otherwise I am pleased with the app.
Kept crashing. I'm waiting for the voice to tell me to stop running and nothing 😡
Excellent
The concept is good, but you can tell it's a GCSE/A level student's project
Enjoyed doing it. I haven't exercised for almost 20 years, but I now can run for 30 minutes and enjoy doing it. Running in short bursts at the start was much more effective than I expected.
Fantastic way to get fitter and healthier 🏃‍♀️
Super helpful. Loved it.
Worked for me , sedentary to running 30minutes non stop 😎
Overall lots of good advice and easy to use. I like that it helps me to take the time out of the day, and I can do that knowing it will always only be for 30 mins!
Great build up to running for beginners!
I'm not a runner at all, but started this to improve cardio fitness. I've really enjoyed it.
Great but only available in English. I'd like a Welsh version please

Overall fantastic for starting running!! I agree with some comments here and give the apps functionality 3/5, but it's main function as a tool to get you running it's easily a 5/5 I can't rate it highly enough. Few bugs (opening other apps when couch to 5k is open causes it to crash), but they're well outweighed by the app. I hated running to now running 5km+ with ease. Might seem too simple/not worth it at the start but stick with it and it really works!
Well this is a suprise. Every week was tough! Can't believe I got to the end. Superb app. Great to be able to listen to your own music. I feel like I havr won the Olympics 😝
Excellent!
I really enjoyed using this app. The intervals and motivation from Jo Whiley were great and helped me keep going to the end!
Fab app really helpful and motivational and instructive
Getting me back to fitness.
Sound not working.

I really like this app, it's simple with no ads and costs nothing. Only give it three stars because each time I have used it ther are glitches in wk 1 which is extremely frustrating. I wouldnt discourage downloading it and giving it a go, I used run 1, wk 1, 3 times instead of risking the glitch in run 2 and 3. Hoping they will fix this ,
Easy to use, does just what I need. Great that you can play your music too
Motivational!!! Ihated running, this app has completely changed my mind
Fantastic!

I had misgivings about whether this would work for me as I struggled to run even for a minute at the start. But completing each stage within the timeframe suggested DID work and nobody is more surprised than me that this turned out to be the case..
Brilliant! I never thought I'd make it to the end, but I did, the guided runs are perfect!

Fantastic app I'm 40 now and decided to to take up running to loose weight and to help with my mood I've not run since I was at school and this app has been awesome in keeping me motivated I'm now running 3 times a week for 30 mins definitely recommend
Not worth the hassle. Once phone locks the app just shuts off. Uninstalled!
Very good App. It's well paced and motivating.

This app is great and motivating. The only problem I have is sometimes it doesn't turn down your music so you can hear the speaker, and also sometimes the music doesn't come back to normal volume after the speaker has finished.
2nd time of using. Brilliant
Great for beginners. Good to give motivation!

Really great app. The running builds up gradually and I found it easy to stick with. Repeated one week twice because it was a bit tough but I did it! That was 5 weeks ago and still running three times a week, up to 45 mins now. On a Samsung A70 and no technical issues for me.
Excellent app, easy to use.
Great app and very achievable if you have a reasonable level of fitness.
Great app! I can't believe I can now run for 30 minutes nonstop! Thoroughly recommend it if you have just started running.

A great way to get motivated especially with the wonderful trainers at your side. I did this from day one with my son who lives 2 hours from me. We just synchronised the start time each day and compared experiences at the end of each run.

This is the best app ever! It has taken me from a 20.5 st non runner to being just under 19 st in 3 months, and being able to jog 5 km (in 41.3 minutes). In the last week I had a couple of technical glitches where the app wouldn't play, but I knew what I had to do and got on with it timing myself 15 mins out and 15 mins in. This app works really well alongside using Strava to map your routes and show you analytics of your pace, and great with a fit bit for tracking fitness. Highly recommended!
The course is set up to be entirely achievable, and the audio gives good encouragement. There are occasional glitches with the audio.
Easy to use app.
Brilliant so far. I'm only on my second wk though, its encouraged me to get out so that's a thumbs up from me.
It keeps crashing mid run. Not very helpful!
Encouraging for beginner
Good motivation easy to use
Supportive and manageable (so far!)

Great app to start running - the first few weeks really ease you into it! Would love to have the option to make my phone vibrate to signal switching between running and walking though! I'd prefer that to wearing headphones.
I've just started running again at the age of 65 after a long time off! I've found this app extremely helpful. I particularly love have Michael Johnsons' voice to keep me going!
Only just started but great so far 😃
Started slowly to build confidence and fitness. After week 5 the mentor came in at just the right moments. Excellent.
Very steady way to build up your ability. I had Sarah Milligans voice coaching me very supportive.
Fabulous! Helped a lot to keep me motivated.
Great experience.
Motivation I needed
I can't believe it--i went from running one minute to running a 5k in 30 minutes. Thank you!!
I thought I did not enjoy running but this app.starts so gently and with the right approach and encouragement. I now look forward to running.
Really motivational.... I've never been able to run, but now I feel I might actually be able to do it!!
Fun and Motivating
Great motivation to keep you on track.
Loved it i have gone from couch to 5k . Week 1 I thought no chance now week 7 running 25 mins no rest 💪
Motivation!
Fantastic
So far it's been easy to use and you can choose who motivates you.
Love it. So nice to hear a familiar voice encouraging you along.
Brilliant way to get into running. App really easy to use

It took me a while to get to grips with how the app worked alongside my music. Once sorted, pretty easy. Found some weeks were a big jump to longer running times so maybe develop another app with a longer programme - maybe 12 weeks - to build up strength and stamina. It is a struggle to do 30mins by the end of this programme and sometimes I feel more deflated than positive at the end of the jog.

Agreeing with a lot of the criticisms already mentioned. Concept is great, but after only installing yesterday I have already encountered multiple problems. It makes my other Apps crash, rendering them unusable. The first run I went on, it paused and when I went back into the App I had to re-start the run again, fast forward and try to guess where I was up to. Also, audio is too quiet against music with no option to adjust. Will try again, but if the problem persists I will be uninstalling.
Brillaint app, it really helps you improve your fitness at a decent rate without throwing you in the deep end whilst making you feel like you're really achieving something.
Excellent inspiring app.
Excellent. Some times coach stoped talking which was annoying
It works, it's supportive and helpful.
Excellent for motivation
Completed C25K... Credit to the app for inspiration. Also lost 2 stone in the process. Ready for some trails now...
Kept me running 🏃‍♀️
I've always been afraid of running and this app helped me overcome the fear! I still don't like running, but I can do it now anyway 😊
I am still in shock that I can run for half an hour. The stages are well planned and the app is easy to use
This is great!!! I just finished the training <3
Brilliant program! I can now run for 30 minutes though not yet fast enough to get a full 5k done in that time. Would be great to see add on content to either improve on time or distance!
Very good step by step training
Well structured

This app is just amazing. At age 53 and having never ran in my life before its enabled me to now run 5k. Didn't think I'd ever be able to do it as could hardly run for a minute on my first time out. Its been so gradual and you are eased in so gently that it's achievable. So don't hesitate, do it today, you won't be disappointed.
Works well with music
Great way to get you into running again
Seems simple and does what it says on the tin. Too early to really tell yet.
really good app!
My only negative is that I'm 54 and can not run 5k in 30 minutes. Perhaps it should be called Couch to 30 minutes. I feel rather flat having only run 4k in the time.
Never thought I would be jogging, am on my 3rd week and I love it
Nice

Great app with small increases in distance. I couldn't run before it and just completed my third 5k feeling good. It took me two years in total, but can take you 9 weeks if you do it as intended. The voice is also nice and helpful, I used Jo wiley voice. It doesn't give you distance runner, so I use another app at the same time to measure my distance and make sure it is 5km. Only problem is that with my Huawei phone the app would close itself if not constantly kept open and waking the screen up.
Worked for me. Great app

Love the app. Very easy to use,no an necessary stuff.I can listen to music and when voice is on music goes a bit queter. It's is so nice you can pick a voice. I hate running but I am on my second week. Thank you so much
A great app to increase stamina

A brilliant app to get you running I'm not a fan of running so this is the perfect encouragement to get you going. I did this in the first lock down and the kept going twice a week. Over the colder weather I didn't do (I'm a fairweather person) but recently started again on week 6 and its great motivation...like a best running partner in your ears!
This is a great gentle introduction to running. The only thing stopping you achieving your goal is you!
Keeps me motivated. Great structure to achieve improved running.
Great app! Works really well with BBC Sounds as well
Love that you can hear your coach over your own music/audio book

Does what I need. I'm on week 2 and I'm finding it enjoyable and motivational so far. I'm using Jo Whiley as a coach but had a few false starts with coaches I didn't gel with. I like the incremental increase in running because this is what I want...just to be able to run for longer. Anyone looking to actually run 5k might need to manage pace a bit more because the app in the final week focuses on time, not distance. Slower paced runners might not cover 5k in that time.
Getting me running again!
Got me, a 68 year old woman, back running. Brilliantly designed in achievable stages
App not reliable and keeps crashing partway through the run.
Awesome
Really helped me get back into running but you've got to stick with the programme
Could not recommend more - absolutely fantastic. Took me from a complete non-runner to 5k in 9 weeks.
I haven't run since at school but now this app has helped me take small steps so far. Thanks
Great app, got me running 30 mins straight in just nine weeks, highly recommend
Very good excercie app
Great app if you really are a couch potato like me! Very easy to start.
Just done first week. It's a good way to start- nice and gentle and a bit hard at the same time!

Great app. Several things it would be good if you could fix. First, there's often a bug, a least on my phone, when I try to start a run, whereby it can't access my trainer. To make it work I have to select another trainer, and then choose my trainer again. Second, it would be great to be told at the start when I will be updated on time run (ie we'll update you at 10, 20 and 25 minutes). Third, please don't say 'well done' 1 minute before the end - I thought I'd finished! But overall, great!
Its a great app to help you train.
Very good and encouraging way to get back fitness
Brilliant, helped me to get back into running
Great to get you into shape
Easy to use and motivating
Would be a fantastic app if it worked properly! Keeps closing itself, or pausing. On the plus side, I kept running for about 4 minutes before I realised 🤦‍♀️
I didn't think it was possible but I have just completed this, from struggling to run for 1 minute in the first week I can now run for 30 minutes! Give it a go, it really works!
Such an easy way to feel good and get fit. Simple instructions to get you through the runs.
Very motivating.
Following a steady program is just what I needed after an injury, a great motivator. Aiming for the park runs when they return 👍
First time I've run in 35 years. Cycled but not run. On week 7 running for 25mins. 7 weeks ago would have been heart attack city
Great been doing it for 4 weeks love the voice letting you how your doing i have Micheal Johnson very inspiring😁
Brilliant
This app saved me from procrastination. Thank you NHS
Love it
Great motivation to get moving
This is quite simply brilliant. I can't imagine anyone less inspired than I am but it's got me running! And it feels safe, which is good news for an oldie like me.
Would be better if you could play music while running rather than silence
I didn't think it would ever be possible to run 5k but this app made it possible
Very motivating to keep you on track
Good to hear the voice keeps you going
Wasnt able to keep up to 3 runs a week due to shift work & young family, but pushed myself to run when I could. Programme took me 4 months to complete but I now run 5k 2 time a week!!!
Really good app. Enjoying my third week!
Talking when to start and ✋
Worked well for me.
Great app. Only disappointment is Sarah Millican stops coaching at week 4. Not enough to mark the app down by a whole star? I am irrational when it comes to Sarah Millican.
Found it a good motivation tool. Give it a try.
Clear guidance, motivating. Would like more motivation during the running periods and more variations.
Excellent.
Nice and steady, love Sarah Milligan giving me encouragement.
Amazed how by sticking to the programme I have improved my lungs and overll fitness without injury. Half way through and I'm sure I'll achieve 5k. Thank you x

I am someone who has never liked running. Tried this as other sports closed due to Covid lockdown. Just completed week 1 and actually quite enjoyed it. Definitely a sense of achievement, and you're eased into running nice and gently. Looking forward to Week 2.. Several weeks later... Finished it.. Recommend this app to anyone who thinks they can't run..
Does what it says on the tin

Totally shocked and delighted by the successful result of this simple to use app. It does what it says on the tin.....or at least it helps you to run regularly for half an hour; I didn't choose the app. to prepare to compete in races, just to get fitter, so achieving the speed required for 5k in half an hour was irrelevant to me.......and yet; I can!
Amazing app. Couldn't run without it. Few glitches every no and then
Great app

I find this a very motivational app. Personally I have Sarah Millican's voice, which I love because, rather than some amazingly skinny athlete, it has a more ordinary, but motivational, feel. It makes me feel like we can all do it. It definitely pushes you, but that is a good thing, and I have discovered a real love of running because of it. 😀
Really motivational
So far so good, I'm amazed that I have made it to week 2 and looking forward to continuing
Never thought I'd be able to run but this really works.
Excellent app myself and daughter are now running for 30 minutes 😁
Fantastic app, really helps you along the way and gives you motivation 👍😁
So encouraging
Easy to use, worked smoothly, and was very motivating. Recommended.
Brilliant... from a non runner to 5k. I would seriously recommend this app. Kept me motivated, easy to use. Now run regulary 3 x week.

Was only going to try this to keep the kids active while waiting for the kids football to start back up again Did not think we would keep it going and surprised myself as i have never done running before. it helps by breaking it down in to little sections and before you know it you have done what you never thought you could 💯 completely would recommend this app .go on give it a go .
Good motivational speakers
Easy to use, great beginner running app
Excellent app - the plan worked well for me and my wife.
Good way to build up your strength and stamina. Coach of your choice from a varied selection, helps you through it.
Brilliant!
Easy to follow and simple to use app

For an overweight 50yr old who did no exercise this was a great app to get you moving. Don't worry if you cannot run, just push yourself to do what you can and keep it realistic. You may not be doing the full 5km in 30mins by the end of week nine but what you will be doing is a solid 30minutes of exercise, three times a week and for me that was a win! Special thanks to Sarah Millican who made me smile with her encouraging words.

I've now done C25k four times as a result of one illness and two injuries. It works just as well the 4th time as the first. Can't praise it too highly. The steady build-up works well. I thought the big stepup to week 4 might be difficult, but the course had prepared me for it and it turned out to be just another run.
Great app!
Only on week two but it's got me running after an eight year gap and feeling better. I've got Jo in my ear and she's encouraging and jolly but never patronising. Get out there.
I'm 60 and finally getting fit all thru this app. Brilliant plus Sarah Millican too. Love it
Really good I hate running 🏃‍♂️ but tried this and I can feel myself improving.

Fantastic app to get you out and running. Well I'm more of a plodder but if someone told me 9 weeks ago I would able to run for 30 minutes, I would have laughed at them. The tempo is great and Laura has a really easy going manner which spurs you on
Amazing! Definitely recommend!
Great app 👌 I love the choice of the coaches plus the reminder setting. I also like that I can track our progress ☺️
Good motivation

Amazing app for beginners!!! I've always tried to get into running but couldn't even last 30 seconds and I always felt self-concious about stop-starting to get my breath back. There's something a little comforting that it's part of the program to walk and catch your breath between runs. I've just completed week 1 and improved massively. Bring on week 2!!!
Good, structured way to start running, nice and gentle and avoided any strains.
Brilliant!
Excellent app 👍
Fab!!!
Amazing! My first successful couch to 5k and oh my gosh the voice overs are so motivating! I definitely recommend it.
The first few weeks almost killed me. But don't give up once ypu find your rhythm it starts to get easier.
Yes to all not tried yet no get up and go
Great app to help start running!
Great for beginners.
Very good for me ( a non runner) Stopped smoking on new years eve after 35 years, and started couch to 5k app mid January Can now run 5k in 38 mins

As a guy who never enjoyed running this app was a breath of fresh air. The goals are really, really achievable (even for someone like me who couldn't imagine running as far and as long as I can now), I loved my "Coach" (shout out to Sanjeev!) and I would thoroughly recommend this to app to others. I'm so happy that I gave this a shot. It's really changed things for me.
Great app really enjoyed it
Couchto5k helped me to enjoy running. This is a great app.
"General bug fixes" is not a change log.
This app really works, love that you can play your own music. Sometimes the music wouldn't turn down when she spoke but that didn't happen often!
Very effective running app
Easy to use. Good motivation
Delighted
So far so good!!

60 yr old female not run for years. Active Walker, swimmer but lost confidence as a runner following several major surgeries. This app offers the perfect level of incentive and constant encouragement. I have and will again encourage others to take it on.
Brilliant app, great podcast. Would definitely recommend to anyone starting out running.
Great inspiration and user friendly
A good way to get started with running and getting fitter
Really good to encourage you off the sofa and to build up your running gradually over 9 weeks. Pleased with myself for completing it as I was surprised how hard I found it at the start.
The app is great, enjoy working with it. Not happy that I lost ALL data when I had to reset my phone.
Once you lock your phone the app stops working.
Good graduated training regime and it works.
Very well good app to start your fitness
Excellent. Just does the job really well and works with your choice of other audio.
Such a good programme, gently easing you into it and before you know it you're running longer than you thought possible
Doesn't work! I changed the setting as per their instructions and it doesn't work. It catches up if I unlock the screen, but what's the point of an app if you have to do it all manually?
Would recommend the app to anyone trying to get fit

Great app. I wasn't new to running but it had been a while since I'd run 5k! I use the app on runs with my 8 year old son as he wanted to be able to run further. Starts you off very easily and gradually builds on how far you run each time. Would recommend to those who have never run and those who have had a break from it.
Never thought I could run well not very fast but can now do 30mins 5k so I dont think that's too bad always completed my runs even when didnt want too
It has really help with my motivetion and structure! Thank you!

I've run long-ish distances in the past (15 mile Sunday runs), triathlons and marathons, and even in summer 2020 was running 6 slow miles at a time. So impatience was my biggest problem. Covid, injury, and lockdown weight meant taking it really slowly so happy to go on C25k and let Michael Johnson be my trainer until I can get up to longer distances again.
Asthmatic and a stomach disability.. so if I can do it.. why can't you? "Those who say they can and those who say they can't are both usually right, what one are you going to be??"

Excellent app - does exactly what you need it to do. Got me to 5k+ in 9 weeks - something I would have struggled to motivate myself to do otherwise. The app does close occasionally mid run but they have a section in the FAQs for different phone users in how to rectify this if it is occurring. If you seriously want a challenge and are committed this app will get you to the goal!
Wonderful app for complete beginners. It's made me feel so much better about myself
Used this app with ease I am now running 5k
We used this for a virtual group and found it easy to use .. I chose Sarah as my coach 😊
I was nervous, but this small incremental build up helped me to get out. I feel fitter, and happier. I can't recommend it enough. Download it and get out there you won't regret it!
Great app just a bit more motivational talk from the trainers would make this app 5 stars
